CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 24, 1953, pg. 17, reads: "TIME OUT FOR FUN - When Jackie Heller gave a press party at his Carousel Monday, the stars of the current show there indulged in a bit of fun and fancy. Leonard Reed, comedian, accompanied Dolores Parker, left, while she gave with one of the songs which made her winner of the Courier's female singer award.  Looking on are Rosario Imperio, interpretive dance; the former "Brown Bomber" Joe Louis, the star of the show, and Mr. Heller. - Teenie Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dolores Parker standing by microphone, with Leonard Reed on piano, Rosario Imperio in background, boxer Joe Louis wearing pinstriped suit leaning on piano, and club owner Jackie Heller in his Carousel Club
